    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-12-18T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-12-18T13:00:00-05:00" n="533"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d533">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">683.84A/12–1852: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 533<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Israel (<persName corresp="#p_DMB1"
                            type="from">Davis</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d533fn1">Repeated to New York, Damascus, Beirut, Amman,
                        Baghdad, Cairo, London, and Paris; sent by pouch to Ankara, Jidda, and
                        Jerusalem.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tel Aviv</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-12-18T20:00:00+02:00"
                            >December 18, 1952—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>994. <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 902<note n="2" xml:id="d533fn2">
                        <ref target="#d528">Document 528</ref>.</note> and Damascus <gloss
                        target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 411 to Dept.<note n="3" xml:id="d533fn3">
                        <ref target="#d529">Document 529</ref>.</note>
                    <gloss target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss>
                    <persName corresp="#p_SM2">Sharett</persName> confirmed to me today Israel
                    interest in continuing conversations with Syria. He stated “matter by no means
                    dormant” but on contrary subj active consideration. He reminded me that there
                    had been important change in high level milit command namely appointment
                        <persName corresp="#p_MM1">Makleff</persName> to succeed <persName
                        corresp="#p_YMG1">Yadin</persName> as Chief of Staff but stated he
                    understood new milit auths now ready with recommendations which he expects to
                    receive Cabinet consideration within next few days. He stated also that <gloss
                        target="#t_IG1">IG</gloss> wld not have postponed resumption of
                    conversations to await outcome of <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> action on
                    eight-power res if long delay wld have been involved, but since only few days’
                    delay in question he had thought it advisable await outcome before arranging
                    definite date for continuation talks with Syria.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DMB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
